  "title": "Senior Associate/Associate Operations (Kitchen)#SGUnitedjobs",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Purpose</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Support Head (Kitchen) in overseeing the operations of 1 Institutional Kitchen in meals productions, ensuring timely delivery, food safety and quality standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br>\n<strong>Major Duties and Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p>- Assist in the overall management of 1 Institutional Kitchen, ensuring service levels are being met.<br>\n- Oversee the preparation and distribution of meals according to dietary requirements and food hygiene standards.<br>\n- Ensure strict compliance of all relevant food and workplace safety regulations, including follow up on audit recommendations.<br>\n- Co-manage a team of workers and vendors to ensure smooth running of operations.<br>\n- Work with the team and various stakeholders to optimize workers’ productivity and morale.<br>\n- Keep abreast of changes in the food industry, i.e. food safety management, SFA regulations, industry best practices.<br>\n- Execute contingency plans when required.<br>\n- Ensure compliance to risk measures from the risk management framework.<br>\n<strong>Any Other Duties</strong></p>\n<p>- Any other tasks or duties assigned by the Head, Kitchen<br>\n<strong>Requirements </strong></p>\n<p><strong>(</strong>Minimum education and experience profile required by the jobholder to perform the job).</p>\n<p><strong>Education</strong></p>\n<p>- Diploma or professional qualifications in Food &amp; Beverage or Manufacturing Operations.<br>\n<strong>Experience</strong></p>\n<p>- Relevant working experience in a food establishment.<br>\n- Candidate with institutional catering experience is preferred.<br>\n<strong>Skills</strong></p>\n<p>- Details oriented with good organization skills.<br>\n-Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.<br>\n-Good knowledge of food handling, food safety and hygiene standards<br>\n-Proficient in Microsoft Office.<br>\n</p>\n<p><br></p>",
